The paper proposes a novel graph convolutional layer for graph neural networks, which is a popular topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed layer is based on auto-regressive moving average (ARMA) filters, which are commonly used in signal processing and time series analysis (cs.CV, cs.NE). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on various downstream tasks, such as node classification and graph regression (cs.SI).
